NT|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The idea behind |CP|1|FP|2|AT|^*Hhttp://www.bridgeguys.com/Conventions/smolen_convention.html,Smolen^*N|CP||FP||at| is that you would rather have the strong hand be declarer. That is an ok idea, but is not nearly as important as some players think. 

Using Smolen, had partner bid 2@D over my 2@C I would bid 3@S rather than 3@H. That shows 5 HEARTS not 5 spades which is why I said it is confusing.|
PG| ***** 6 ***** |


NT|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|But if you play that convention, then the 1NT bidder gets to be declarer in either 4@H or 3NT. However, if you don't play Smolen then your side ends up in 4@H, responder rather than opener is declarer. 

It is not a big deal IMO, but there is sometimes an advantage to having the NT bidder be declarer.|
